A simple contact

Julio S. Solís Arce

11/11/2020

Imagine we have a very simple theory where contact reduces prejudice through perspective taking. Also, contact, on its own, could affect prejudice (for better or worse). Allport’s conditions are not shown in the DAG since they are moderators.

#Model
N <- 1000 # sample size 
ate_prejudice <- 0.5 # average treatment effect
sd <- 0.2 # sd 


df1 <- ""


population <- 
  declare_population(N = N,
                     prejudice = rnorm(n = N,  mean = .8, sd = sd) %>%
                       round(., 2),
                     perspective = rbinom(N, 5, 0.5),
                     contact = rbinom(N, 1, sd),
                     X=perspective) 

df1 <- population()

potential_outcomes <- declare_potential_outcomes(Y ~ prejudice + ate_prejudice*Z + X, 
                                                 assignment_variables = Z) 
                                                 

df1 <- potential_outcomes(df1)


datatable(df1)
